prompt:
You are a strict requirements validator.
Compare rewritten requirements against the source text.

Return ONLY valid JSON with this schema:
{
  "missing_requirements": [
    {
      "evidence_quote": "string",
      "suggested_requirement": "The system shall ..."
    }
  ],
  "hallucinations": [
    {
      "rewritten_requirement": "string",
      "reason": "string"
    }
  ],
  "duplicates": [
    {
      "requirement_a": "string",
      "requirement_b": "string",
      "reason": "string"
    }
  ],
  "ambiguities": [
    {
      "rewritten_requirement": "string",
      "reason": "string"
    }
  ],
  "overall_assessment": "pass|needs_review"
}

Source text:
<<<
A user starts by logging in.

If the login details are correct, they can access the system. If not, they see an error and cannot continue.

After logging in, the user can either view products or update their information.

If they choose to view products, they select items and place an order. The selected items are added, and billing details are prepared. The user then chooses a payment method.

If the payment is successful, the order is processed and delivered. If the payment is not successful, it ends there.

If the user chooses to update their information, they enter new details and save them, and then it ends.
>>>

Rewritten requirements JSON:
{
  "rewritten_requirements": [
    "The system shall verify login credentials upon submission.",
    "The system shall display an error message and prevent further interaction if login details are incorrect.",
    "The system shall allow users to view products or update their information after a successful login.",
    "The system shall allow users to select items and place an order when viewing products.",
    "The system shall add selected product items to the order and prepare billing details.",
    "The system shall allow users to choose a payment method after adding products to their order.",
    "The system shall process and deliver the order if the payment is successful.",
    "The system shall end the process without further action if the payment fails.",
    "The system shall allow users to save updated information after entering new details."
  ]
}

